whereas.text:
Whereas childhood obesity, undernourishment, and physical
			 inactivity are national epidemics, and schools can help to address these
			 problems by becoming healthier places so kids can live healthier lives;

Whereas 1 in 3 of the Nation’s children are overweight or
			 obese which puts those children at a high risk for developing heart disease,
			 cancer, asthma, and diabetes;

Whereas only 8 percent of elementary school students and 6
			 percent of middle and high school students have daily physical
			 education;

Whereas every child needs a healthy diet consisting of
			 nutritious foods in appropriate portion sizes based on age and
			 development;

Whereas children who eat poorly or who engage in too
			 little physical activity do not perform as well as they should
			 academically;
